!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

flight /flaɪt/

(flights) 

1. N-COUNT A flight is a trip made by flying, usually in an aeroplane. 飞行 

例： The flight will take four hours. 此次飞行将需要四个小时。 

2. N-COUNT You can refer to an aeroplane carrying passengers on a particular trip as a particular flight . 航班 [also N num] 

例： BA flight 286 was two hours late. 英国航空286次航班晚点两个小时。 

3. N-COUNT A flight of steps or stairs is a set of steps or stairs that lead from one level to another without changing direction. 一段 (台阶或楼梯) 

例： We walked in silence up a flight of stairs and down a long corridor. 我们默默地走上一段楼梯，穿过一道长廊。 

4. N-UNCOUNT Flight is the action of flying, or the ability to fly. 飞行; 飞行能力 

例： Supersonic flight could become a routine form of travel in the 21st century. 搭乘超音速飞机飞行会成为21世纪常见的旅行方式。 

5. N-UNCOUNT Flight is the act of running away from a dangerous or unpleasant situation or place. 逃跑 

例： The family was often in flight, hiding out in friends' houses. 这一家人经常逃来逃去，躲藏在朋友们的家里。 

6. N a feather or plastic attachment fitted to an arrow or dart to give it stability in flight 镖尾 

7. N a set of steps or stairs between one landing or floor and the next 一段(台阶或楼梯) 

8. V to cause (a ball, dart, etc) to float slowly or deceptively towards its target 使(球，镖等)慢慢移向目标 [sport]

</div>

